(2) In the course of evaluating the proposed use, the Planning
Director, Planning Board or Town Board of Commissioners may
request additional information from the petitioner. Information
requested may include the following:
(A) The location of significant trees on the petitioned property;
(B) Scale of buildings relative to adjoining properties,
including sight lines;
(C) Height of structures;
(D) Exterior features of proposed development;
(E) Any other information needed to demonstrate compliance
with these regulations.
(3) The site plan, building elevations, perspectives, sections, and
any supporting text shall constitute part of the petition for all
purposes under these regulations.
